      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MCADAM (2) led in a new role last start and he went on to destroy a BM66 field over this distance at Wagga. Takes on some better types today but that recent performance was hard to ignore. Back on his home track and another big run looks assured. ANGEL CITY (9) won two on the bounce then went to Canterbury last time and found the class beyond her. Progressive filly who deserves another chance back in this more suitable assignment. UBER IN (7) made it two wins from her last three outings when she comfortably disposed of a BM58 field over 1300m at Goulburn 12 days ago. New to this trip but there is Zabeel on the dam's side so she gets the benefit of the doubt. SPICE PRAWN (6) faces her easiest essay for quite a while. Form in town has been good enough. Gets back but has the talent to finish over the top of these. BALLPARK (3) wasn't suited first-up at Wyong and can do a lot better under todays' set-up.",
